text: Wadhurst is a town and civil parish in Wealden, East Sussex, South East England. As of June 2018, there were an estimate of 4,036 people living in Wadhurst. Out of which 1,872 were men and 2,164 were women. https://www.citypopulation.de/en/uk/southeastengland/east_sussex/E34004158__wadhurst/ == References == Category:Civil parishes in East Sussex Category:Towns in East Sussex Category:Wealden
